Eric is a psychologist with 20 years of expertise in psychological assessment. Over the years he has been most interested in the behaviors and personality traits that result in people’s success. Human performance attributes underlie everyone’s technical abilities. In January 2019, he released his first book, “The Psychology of Top Talent: The Practical Scientifically Proven Method to Identify, Hire, and Develop High Performers.”

These are the psychological factors that create top talent and high-performing leaders who are loved by their teams.

In addition to coaching individuals and organizations on these topics, he spends a significant amount of his professional time curating psychological research, writing about its applications on human performance, and developing strategies and protocols to help top professionals consistently push their potential.
